docs.text: Home About Me I deal mainly with offensive security. I like to do CTFs and do random sysadmin things in my homelab. In the process of getting spun up with traditional defensive security. About the Blog This blog is here primarily to help me document and further solidify lessons learned, while hopefully benefiting others as well. Social Social links are down below, but I'm not very active currently. I do a lot of commits to GitHub, though. CTFs and Write-Ups I do my best to document my process. If I have incomplete sections, I'm likely still working on it. I'll finish it!
